@jgwithice Yep. The core product is fine. I could talk in a lot of depth about this, but 2 brief points:

1. However good central contacts are, the link between county cricket and the England setup has been weakened.

2. Sunday League/NatWest Trophy on BBC was a great ad for county cricket.

@TheDaveBrookes There are two big questions nobody has definitively been able to answer:

1. What length of time immunity does having the vaccine give you? A few months? A year? More? Less?

2. How effective will the vaccine be against new and future strains?

@acbwodahs I think people are being lured into a false sense of security. The two key questions we don't know the answers to are:

1. What period of time does the vaccine immunity last?

2. How effective will the vaccine be against future strains?

@glennerboy That's right. There's also another BIG factor: The wider world.

South Sudan has plenty of vaccine supplies, but the number of people willing to have it is minuscule. Other countries will be in a similar position.

Normal travel etc will not resume until it's dealt with globally.

