@glennerboy 1. It's clear the current variants of covid are affecting younger people far more than earlier strains.

2. Travel won't return to normal until the whole world is inoculated.  That's a long way off.

3. We don't know how effective the vaccine will be against future strains.

@TOchemaster I know a young person (a decade younger than me) who is seriously ill right now. 

As for reinfection - we don't know. Six months? A year? What about new variants?

The vaccine is VERY welcome but it's not a 'magic bullet' out of this.

@TOchemaster Two million was the aim, though the reality is somewhat lower (though it's still hugely successful outside Scotland).

The theory of 'herd immunity' is wobbly to say the least. Plus we need to consider new strains, which the vaccine may not offer immunity to. 

It's complex.

@j_slatman Two things I'd do:

1. Make everyone use their real names and provide verifiable ID when signing up. 

2. Give the police the powers to issue social media firms with a bill every time they have to spend time and resources investigating activity on social media.

